*a>>2 = value of a is shifted towards right 2 times without digits 
on the left getting replaced ,they only get reduced

*a<<2 = value of a is shifted towards left 2 times with digits 
on the left getting replaced with 0;

*people say a>>>2 = value of a is shifted towards right 2 times with digits 
on the left getting replaced with 0;

*to store an octal value of a number in int use 
int a=016 //0 is important

*to store hexadecimal value of a number in integer use
eg
int a=0x56// ox is important

*a>>=2 means a=a>>2;
similarly others also

